New Records: Victor Wembanyama had a career-high 50 points.
Wembanyama set a career high by making 8 three-pointers.
At 20 years 314 days, Wembanyama is the fourth-youngest player to score 50 points.
Wembanyama is the first player in league history with 20 three-pointers and 25 blocks over a six-game span.
Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama scored 50 points to help the San Antonio Spurs defeat the Washington Wizards 139-130.
Jordan Poole scored 42 points for the Washington Wizards.
Wembanyama made an 18-foot jumper for his 49th and 50th points with 8:49 remaining to give San Antonio a 115-98 lead.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Wembanyama is the eighth player in San Antonio Spurs franchise history to score 50 points.
David Robinson holds the franchise record with 71 points against the Los Angeles Clippers on April 24, 1994.
